text.tspan: Stoicism (Passive) - Dominic is immune to stuns.
Gatling Gun (8) - Fires bullets that deal 50 pure damage to target enemy
as well as 30 pure damage to all units behind it.
Focus (6) - Increases the damage of the next attack by 100%. This buff
lasts two turns (and is therefore stackable twice).
Chen (10) - Heals all allied units (including Dominic) for 50 + STR + INT
health. After this spell is used, Dominic receives Drain for three turns.
Advice: Dominic has an interesting power curve. The Gatling Gun + Focus
combination, though dealing pure damage, falls off with no stat scaling. That
being said, Dominic is the only character who is outright immune to stuns,
and combined with Chen and his great stat gain, he can tank well.
Granite Kick (10) - Deals damage equal to 5STR and stuns for one turn.
Blood Transfer (10) - Grants three stamina to all units in the active party.
Body Transfer (5) - At the cost of 50 health, Yongwoon heals the target ally
for 5STR. Damage dealt to Yongwoon is lethal.
Advice: Yongwoon is capable of absorbing plenty of physical damage, but
his lack of defense leaves him vulnerable to magic attacks. While Granite
Kick and Blood Transfer are expensive, his high speed compensates for this.
Body Transfer has exceptional scaling, and Yongwoon's health pool is high
enough for it to be frequently used. Like many others with expensive skills,
Yongwoon is weak to Drain. Any amount of defense boost will dramatically
Barrier (5) - Increases the defense of a target ally by five for four turns.
CAD Imprisonment (8) - Inflicts Bind on all enemy units for three turns.
Vocal Boom (8) - Inflicts Mute on all enemy units for three turns.
Friendship is Magic (10) - Swap three party members this turn.
Advice: Kenji doesn't have damage-dealing abilities, but that doesn't mean he
isn't useful. Barrier is a quick and effective defensive tool. CAD Imprisonment
and Vocal Boom are some of the longest lasting area disables in the game,
which can force the enemy to swap out at inconvenient times. Speaking of
swapping out, Friendship is Magic is the fastest party-swapping mechanic
in the game. As always, characters with expensive skills are vulnerable to
Stone Limbs (Passive) - Haley is immune to Drain.
Whirling Kick (3) - Deals 2STR + 15 damage to two front enemies.
Dash (5) - Deals 2STR + 10 damage to all enemies (Row).
Unravel (3) - Haley removes Bind from herself.
Mountain Chisel (10) - Haley launches a flurry of attacks at a
Advice: Haley is immune to Drain and can remove Bind, leaving
her vulnerable only to Mute. Her defense is excellent but her
lackluster health means she probably can't tank. Haley's rapid
damage shines against units with low defenses.
Fortress (6) - Doubles DEF. Bind is incurred while active.
Totem of Earth (10) - Stuns all enemy units for two turns. Katherine incurs
Stun and Drain for two turns.
Obliteration (10) - Katherine sacrifices 50% of her current health, dealing
pure damage equal to twice the amount of health sacrificed, to all enemies.
Universal Purge (10) - Removes Bind, Mute, and Drain from all allied units.
Katherine incurs Stun and Drain indefinitely or until removed.
Advice: Katherine's skills are extremely powerful but can result in her own
death if not used in conjunction with proper status removal and healing.
Drain, Mute and stamina removal prevent Katherine from functioning. It's up
to you to find a situation where her abilities go unchecked.
Analyze (5) - The target ally ignores DEF on the next attack.
Decipher (5) - The target ally gains immunity to the next status effect.
Cripple (8) - Deals 4INT + 20 damage to target enemy. The enemy is also
inflicted with Bind and Mute for two turns.
Deep Purge (8) - Removes Mute from all allied units. Castable while muted.
Advice: Christine has solid status control. Decipher may be used on a tank
preemptively, and Deep Purge offers a hard-to-counter solution to Mute.
Analyze is a great all-purpose damage buff, and Cripple has impressive
damage and disable. Try to keep Christine toward the back -- her health and
defenses aren't great -- and find a way to increase her speed if you can.
